  ANIMALS OF THE WORLD
============================================================

Name:         Blue Whale
Scientific:   Balaenoptera musculus
Class:        Mammalia
Habitat:      Ocean
Diet:         Carnivore (krill)
Lifespan:     80 years
Weight:       150000 kg
Status:       Endangered
Fact:         Largest animal ever known; heart is size of a small car

Name:         Emperor Penguin
Scientific:   Aptenodytes forsteri
Class:        Aves
Habitat:      Antarctic
Diet:         Carnivore
Lifespan:     25 years
Weight:       45 kg
Status:       Near Threatened
Fact:         Deepest-diving bird at 565m; male incubates egg 65 days without eating

Name:         Pistol Shrimp
Scientific:   Alpheidae
Class:        Malacostraca
Habitat:      Tropical ocean
Diet:         Carnivore
Lifespan:     3 years
Weight:       0.001 kg
Status:       Least Concern
Fact:         Snapping claw creates bubble briefly hotter than the sun's surface

============================================================
  DISEASES & MEDICINE
============================================================

Disease:     Hepatitis B
Type:        Viral
Pathogen:    HBV
Transmission:Blood, sexual contact
Symptoms:    Often asymptomatic; jaundice
Treatment:   Antivirals (tenofovir)
Deaths/yr:   0.82M
Vaccine:     Yes (highly effective)
Discovered:  1965

Disease:     Cardiovascular Disease
Type:        Metabolic
Pathogen:    Non-communicable
Transmission:Non-communicable
Symptoms:    Chest pain, shortness of breath
Treatment:   Statins, surgery, stents
Deaths/yr:   17.9M
Vaccine:     No (for most types)
Discovered:  Ancient

Disease:     COVID-19
Type:        Viral
Pathogen:    SARS-CoV-2
Transmission:Respiratory droplets
Symptoms:    Fever, cough, loss of smell
Treatment:   Antivirals, supportive care
Deaths/yr:   5.0M
Vaccine:     Yes (mRNA vaccines)
Discovered:  2019

